declarations.description:
Alternative to Polymer's dom-if element that allows comparison between two operands, as well as progressive enhancement.
DOM deletion takes place on non matching elements.
declarations.name: IfDiffThenStiff

members.description: Must be true to pass test(s). Can also be an object.  Condition is based on the property being truthy.
members.name: iff

members.description: LHS Operand.
members.name: lhs

members.description: Iff property has to be a non empty array.
members.name: isNonEmptyArray

members.description: RHS Operand.
members.name: rhs

members.description: lhs must equal rhs to pass tests.
members.name: equals

members.description: Do not evaluate expression until disabled setting is removed.
members.name: disabled

members.description: If content is rendered by the server, the server can indicate which nodes that it rendered can be hidden / displayed by if-diff on the client.
members.name: ownedSiblingCount

members.description: Specify exact manner in which non-visible content should be hidden.
members.name: hiddenStyle

members.description: Specify name of attribute to add when conditions are satisfied / removed when not satisfied
members.name: setAttr

members.description: Specify name of class to add when conditions are satisfied / removed when not satisfied
members.name: setClass

members.description: Specify name of part to add when conditions are satisfied / removed when not satisfied
members.name: setPart

members.description: lhs must not equal rhs to pass tests.
members.name: notEquals

members.description: For strings, this means lhs.indexOf(rhs) > -1.  For arrays, this means lhs intersect rhs = rhs. For numbers, this means lhs >= rhs.  For objects, this means all the properties of rhs match the same properties of lhs
members.name: includes

members.description: Maximum number of elements that are effected by condition.
members.name: m

members.description: Additional condition for a media query to be added for tests to be satisfied.
members.name: andMediaMatches
